<item>
            <title>[CXF-5157] JAXRS JAASAuthenticationFilter not rfc2617 compliant for WWW-Authenticate realms</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-5157</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The JAASAuthenticationFilter not rfc2617 compliant for WWW-Authenticate realms.  Currently the returned headers for a realm called &quot;foo&quot; would return:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Basic foo&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, according to rfc2617 p2/3 it states: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The authentication parameter realm is defined for all authentication&lt;br/&gt;
   schemes:&lt;br/&gt;
      realm       = &quot;realm&quot; &quot;=&quot; realm-value&lt;br/&gt;
      realm-value = quoted-string&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefor the above example is supposed to look like the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Basic realm=&quot;foo&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will make the JAX-RS authentication compliant with the rfc and also compatible with other implementations such as Jetty.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
